{:title "Minimal Agent Kernel"
 :description "Refactor mcp-injector to act as a semi-transparent kernel that handles internal tools recursively before handing off to Gateway."
 :acceptance-criteria
 ["Kernel executes internal tools (mcp__*, clojure-eval, get_tool_schema) and recurs."
  "Kernel hands off to Gateway ONLY when tool batch is 100% passthrough tools."
  "PII is restored for trusted tools at the membrane (last second before exec/handoff)."
  "All tool results are redacted before being added to history."
  "Mixed batches result in internal execution followed by recursion (Strict Priority)."]
 :edge-cases
 ["Malformed JSON tool arguments do not crash the kernel."
  "Mixed internal/passthrough batches do not leak half-baked context to Gateway."
  "Trust rules (:block) are honored at the passthrough handoff boundary."]
 :depends-on [:pii-restoration :governance-hardening]}
